73. his: instrumental ablative. tibi: dative of the agent with dicatur. Grynei nemoris: 126. of Grynia, in Mysia, where Apollo had a temple. Euphorion of Chalcis wrote a poem about this temple, which Gallus seems to have imitated. dicatur: distinguish from dicatur, “ it is being dedicated.’'

76. Dulichias : ie. of Ulysses, who was said by some to have ruled over the island of Dulichium as well as the neighbouring Ithaca.

86. iussit : the subject is vesper. invito . . . Olympo ε “from Olympus despite Olympus' reluctance.'' The omission of the prepo- sition is common in poetry. Vesper (the evening star) was thought to rise on Mount Olympus. Even Olympus is unwilling that evening should come on and the song cease.
